track_notes: Well used trails both up and down, but up is rather steep.

This is the Hard Way route, specially in winter time, it goes trough a very steep -Canyon- moutain lot open in the middle, in winter was much ice under the snow. On the way down I took the longest track.
There are many ways to this summit from diferent rutes.


-

I like to Check-inn as close as possible from the summit, and within the 25m zone as stated in the SOTA rules.
(Typically the contour line is 25 metres below peak height of the summit).

I use several apps: SOTA Goat Summit Tracker, APRS/GPS tracking, etc. most of the time depending of battery status on the phone, and all other equipment when I am at work or SOTA.
Specially on winter time when is down to -10/-25 degrees, my company 3y+ old iPhone does not have battery capacity as before. 

I have over 100K+++ pictures private and work related, 03/2024 I started to convert tracks and pics into database time allowing, as I travel a lot due to my work.

After I took the hardest way up, not possible to take the same way down specially in winter time, too dangerous, so this is the best way down in winter, in summer I do not know. 03/2+024 was too much snow and ice still all around.
track_title: LA/BU-027 Route way down by LA9PJA
